The paper discusses the security threats and vulnerabilities in SD-WAN, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the need for secure software development life cycle (SSDLC) and secure design of SD-WAN solutions, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper explores various vendor features and their security, which falls under the category of systems and information theory (cs.SI).
